In general, developed Asian economies (represented only by Japanese companies) have adopted most of the SDGs (relative frequency
r = 0 . 948
) (see the last column of Table 2). These companies strongly emphasise fulfilling 16 out of the 17 SDGs on average, and no less-preferred SDG was identified for this group. Companies from all other economies prefer to concentrate on a limited number of SDGs (relative frequency r varies between 0.397 and 0.503).
